Fairview 20-12-19 Best Bet Race 5 No 1 King Capone Although the Jacques Strydom-trained King Capone remains a maiden after seven tries, he has recorded three close-up seconds and a third from his last five appearances so you can’t deny the fact he is a decent thoroughbred. The manner in which he finished off his most recent appearance – running on from near last passing the 300m marker – to finish an eye-catching second behind Buzz World strongly suggests he is begging for this 2400m trip. Although drawn worst of all, this ultra-consistent three-year-old by far has the best form...